		strong Bringing the data together:

	p Right now, the project information that is disclosed is often very scattered - reported in fragmentary tables in PDF reports, or mixed together with aggregate country, company and corporate group information. It is difficult to find the relationships between projects, contracts, companies and corporate groups.
	p
		|Through this prototype we have established
		a(href='/model')  data model
		=' for bringing together data on countries, companies, projects, and payments related to them. We are adding support for license, contract and concession information, building a rich'
		a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linked_data')  linked data
		=' platform.'
	p Data from a number of sources has been loaded into the prototype, showing how we can bring together multiple project level reports to get a more comprehensive view of the extractives industry.
	p The platform currently provides

	ul
		li
			p A simple spreadsheet template for data creation, making it easy to research and transcribe project level information;
		li
			p Common identifiers for key entities, including projects, companies and corporate groups - supporting linkage between datasets;
		li
			p A browse interface onto existing project-level reports loaded to the platform;
		li
			p Full provenance information, allowing data-points to be traced back to their source;

